                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/38314",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=seferovic",
                        "name": "seferovic",
                        "displayName": "Edvin Seferovic",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Artur it would be great if you could look into this problem, because it is a real blocker (for me). \r\n\r\nI need hostname based routing for my modules and the only \"half\"-workaround Ive managed to produce is following...\r\n\r\n$hostnameRoute = new Zend_Controller_Router_Route_Hostname('admin.test.local',array('module' => 'admin'));\r\n\r\n\/\/ Instead of empty static route...      \r\n\/\/ $oRoute = new Zend_Controller_Router_Route_Static('');\r\n       \r\n$oRoute = new Zend_Controller_Router_Route('\/:controller\/:action\/*',\r\n                                           array('module'     => 'admin',\r\n                                                 'controller' => 'index',\r\n                                                 'action'     => 'index'));\r\n                                                 \r\n$router->addRoute('admin', $hostnameRoute->chain($oRoute));\r\n\r\nWith this Ive managed the routing part... but in the routing process the path information is build without \"\/\" at the beginning. $this->_request->getPathInfo() returns \"controller\/action\" instead of \"\/controller\/action\" This breaks the Zend_Navigation component !!\r\n\r\nMaybe there is another workaround I am not aware of?",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=seferovic",
                        "name": "seferovic",
                        "displayName": "Edvin Seferovic",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-02-06T18:55:24.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-02-06T18:55:24.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/38386",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=joust",
                        "name": "joust",
                        "displayName": "Artur Bodera",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Hey Edvin!\r\n\r\nWhich version are you using?\r\nHave you patched your ZF with the snippets I provided?\r\n\r\nI use these routes (suggested by docs, sic!) every day and they work fine.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=joust",
                        "name": "joust",
                        "displayName": "Artur Bodera",
                        "active": true
